This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 12-18, 2010, as National Historically Black Colleges and Universities Week. It highlights the importance of Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCUs) in providing higher education opportunities for African Americans and their contributions to the growth and progress of the nation. The proclamation also mentions the efforts to strengthen the White House Initiative on HBCUs and increase their capacity to provide quality education to more students. It calls upon public officials, educators, librarians, and Americans to observe the week with programs and activities that acknowledge the achievements of HBCUs and their graduates.